This paper discusses the development of a test to measure reading comprehension ability, which is a core component of literacy. It also explores the emerging field of artificial intelligence and its ability to read and understand like humans. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Learning), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
